ll `semanticIndexService.indexEntity(\\\"commit\\\", savedCommit.getId())`. Inject SemanticIndexService via constructor (optional dependency — use `@Autowired(required=false)` or just inject and null-check).\\n- `ScopeChangeService.java`: after creating a ScopeChangeEvent, call indexEntity(\\\"scope_change\\\", event.getId()).\\n- `CarryForwardService.java`: after creating a CarryForwardLink, call indexEntity(\\\"carry_forward\\\", link.getId()).\\n- `ManagerReviewService.java`: after creating a ManagerComment, call indexEntity(\\\"manager_comment\\\", comment.getId()).\\n- `TicketService.java`: after create/update, call indexEntity(\\\"ticket\\\", workItem.getId()).\\n- `LockService.java`: after locking a plan, call indexEntity(\\\"plan_summary\\\", plan.getId()). Also inject `InsightGenerationService` (from step-7, but add the field + null-check now with `@Autowired(required=false)`) and after a successful lock call `insightGenerationService.generatePersonalInsightsAsync(plan.getId())` — this triggers personal insight generation when a plan is finalized. The actual `InsightGenerationService` class is created in step-7; for now, the field is null and the null-check skips the call, keeping tests green.\\n- `ReconciliationService.java`: after reconcile submit, call indexEntity(\\\"plan_summary\\\", plan.getId()).\\n\\nThe `@Async` annotation on `indexEntity()` ensures these calls don't block the write path. Since `@EnableAsync` was added in step-1, Spring will proxy the calls.\\n\\nNo separate test file needed for SemanticIndexService in this step — it will be indirectly tested. But ensure existing tests pass since we're modifying service constructors (use `@Autowired(required=false)` or default null for the new SemanticIndexService dependency so existing mocked tests don't break).\",\n  \"requiredChecks\": [\n    \"build\",\n    \"unit\"\n  ]\n}\n\nYou are the first agent to work on this step.\nImplement the changes described above, run checks to verify, and fix any